# Golden Server

An MCP server scaffolded with [Dockyard](https://github.com/hurtener/dockyard).

## Layout

- `dockyard.app.yaml` — the manifest (server identity, tools, quality gates).
- `main.go` — the entrypoint: constructs the server, serves stdio.
- `greet.go` — the example `greet` tool and its handler.
- `greet_test.go` — a contract test for the example tool.
- `internal/contracts/` — the typed Go contract structs (the source of
  truth, P1) plus their **generated** JSON Schema and TypeScript. Never
  hand-edit a generated file; change the Go struct and regenerate.

## Run

```sh
go run .                          # serve over stdio (the default)
DOCKYARD_TRANSPORT=http go run .   # serve the streamable-HTTP transport
go test ./...                     # run the contract tests
```

## Next steps

- Add a tool: write a handler and a `tool.New(...)` call in `greet.go`.
- Edit a contract: change the struct in `internal/contracts`, then
  regenerate the schema with `dockyard generate`.
- Validate the project with `dockyard validate`.

## Optional OAuth protection for HTTP

HTTP is unauthenticated by default. To make it an OAuth protected resource,
configure `server.HTTPOptions.Authorization` as shown in
[`examples/oauth-resource-server`](https://github.com/hurtener/dockyard/tree/main/examples/oauth-resource-server).
The example reads the canonical resource URL, trusted issuer, required scopes,
and continuation key from the environment and rejects partial or unsafe
configuration. It does not change the default stdio or HTTP behavior.
